I had been tracking this particular pack for nearly a week now. I had found them at the base of the mountain as I had descended, and oddly enough must have been skirting their range as I traveled. There were six of them: the two parents and their four pups. The pups could not have been more than a year old; they were probably just learning how to hunt. I sometimes spied them still engaging in the way young wolves did, playing and yipping while their parents looked on, as if wishing they would pay more attention to what was going on around them. The patriarch was a good looking wolf by any hunter&#039;s measure. He was well-built and able-bodied; the only thing wrong I could see was a bald spot on his left thigh, caused by a scar. Everywhere he went, he was flanked by the matriarch of the pack, and she was always scanning the forest with an icy gaze that -- that reminded me of...
 
